(34, 3, '2015-04-16 23:52:15', '2015-04-16 23:52:15', 'Piloting XP traces Motorola''s experiment with extreme programming applied to mission-critical software projects. Four development teams worked for 18 months on four different projects; the teams used extreme programming practices as their guideline, modifying the process to fit their needs as appropriate. An outside consultant, or "coach", was brought to ensure that the extreme programming processes was being used properly. The extreme programming process was chosen for its ability to adapt to changing requirements; development projects at Motorola had a history of fixed completion dates, dynamic requirements, and development beginning before said requirements were fixed.\n\nExtreme programming is a documentation-light process. Features for the software were documented as use cases, which were written by the customers, submitted to Motorola''s technical-review process, and delivered to the development team. The teams also used a high-level architecture design document to supplement understanding of the code base. At the end of each iteration, the architecture document was updated to reflect the changes made to the code base. The architecture document was then reviewed by the team, independent object-oriented experts, and outsiders to the team.\n\nQualitative results were obtained through a survey distributed to all members of the extreme programming teams. The survey measured the benefits of extreme programming on the following criteria: morale, learning, productivity, test coverage, quality and maintainability, and how well the process was followed. Productivity was measured in KAELOC - thousands of assembler-equivalent lines of code - over staff effort. All extreme programming teams showed increased productivity over existing waterfall teams; two of the extreme programming teams were over three times as productive as the waterfall teams. The teams obtained between 73 - 95% unit test code coverage. The teams also experienced a 51 - 74% increase in quality, measured in total defects found / KAELOC. These and other metrics led to the conclusion that extreme programming can be successfully applied to mission-critical projects with long life-spans, with significant benefits.', 'Piloting XP on Four Mission-Critical Projects', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '%d0%bf%d1%80%d0%b8%d0%b2%d0%b5%d1%82-%d0%bc%d0%b8%d1%80', '', '', '2015-04-16 23:52:15', '2015-04-16 23:52:15', '', 0, 'http://zolga.com.ua/?p=1', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(35, 3, '2015-04-16 23:52:15', '2015-04-16 23:52:15', 'Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Vivamus congue congue augue, at tincidunt quam lacinia nec. Morbi non finibus risus, ut eleifend orci. Pellentesque ac diam sit amet mi gravida dapibus sed a sem. Ut volutpat augue mi, quis finibus tortor tempor eget. Nam eget lacus urna. Morbi nec mollis nibh, in malesuada purus. Vivamus sed enim vitae sapien consequat posuere. Nam et sagittis dui, at facilisis ante. Pellentesque sem leo, semper a libero sed, sagittis aliquam nulla. Nam varius luctus libero, sed placerat magna ultricies at. Donec accumsan a purus vitae consectetur. Nulla iaculis, nibh vel elementum malesuada, lacus dui posuere nibh, a placerat mi odio ut leo. Nunc sed nisl nunc. Nam lacinia dictum odio, eget blandit tellus ultrices et.\n\nUt placerat tincidunt tellus, sed semper quam suscipit eu. Aenean tempor laoreet libero non faucibus. Vestibulum blandit consectetur laoreet. Mauris enim risus, cursus at aliquam ut, porta in risus. Nunc at euismod mauris, eu placerat orci. Sed et nisi tortor. Sed et fermentum dolor. Aliquam erat volutpat. Nunc at egestas sapien, nec lobortis nisi. Fusce dictum pulvinar vulputate. Nam id sollicitudin nisi. Donec non porta ligula. Phasellus sagittis euismod ipsum vitae porttitor.\n\nUt finibus ligula sit amet dui pellentesque malesuada. Aliquam ut sapien risus. Etiam fringilla sem sed metus mattis, dapibus tempus massa consectetur. Pellentesque iaculis ultrices orci at tincidunt. Fusce felis lectus, imperdiet in sem quis, imperdiet lacinia metus. Interdum et malesuada fames ac ante ipsum primis in faucibus. Mauris vehicula massa non aliquet pulvinar.', 'About us', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'sample-page-2', '', '', '2015-04-16 23:52:15', '2015-04-16 23:52:15', '', 0, 'http://zolga.com.ua/?page_id=2', 0, 'page', '', 0),
